<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="1181" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1181">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.63/30.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Minister to
                                    Mexico</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-28">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 28, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>192. Department’s 297. Government advised today that regulations as
                            contained in circular of September 3 shall apply. Said circular was
                            mailed you September 29. Am mailing full translation of note.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>